d's%20first%20franchisee%20and%20transformed%20the%20restaurant%20into%20a%20global%20empire.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20McDonald%20brothers%20opened%20their%20small%20restaurant%20in%201940%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthen-and-now-mcdonalds-menu-items-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimple%20menu%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20burgers%2C%20fries%2C%20and%20beverages%20like%20their%20%26quot%3BTriple%20Thick%20Milkshakes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERay%20Kroc%2C%20a%20Multimixer%20salesman%2C%20saw%20the%20restaurant's%20potential%20and%20became%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthen-and-now-mcdonalds-restaurants-through-the-years%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20franchise%20agent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201955%2C%20Kroc%20founded%20McDonald's%20System%2C%20Inc.%2C%20which%20would%20later%20become%20the%20McDonald's%20Corporation.%20He%20bought%20out%20the%20brothers%20in%201961%20for%20%242.7%20million%2C%20the%20equivalent%20of%20about%20%2428.5%20million%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20timeline%20showing%20how%20Ray%20Kroc%20built%20McDonald's%20from%20a%20small%20burger%20joint%20to%20a%20global%20fast-food%20empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1902%3A%20Ray%20Kroc%20was%20born%20in%20Oak%20Park%2C%20Illinois%2C%20on%20October%205.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222023%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ray%20Kroc%20McDonald's%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6776df91e5726ab18d0e5066%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221517%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERay%20Kroc%20was%20credited%20with%20launching%20McDonald's%20from%20a%20small%20restaurant%20to%20a%20global%20fast-food%20empire.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FContributor%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.biography.com%2Fbusiness-leaders%2Fray-kroc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBiography%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%2